man! to think’s audacity. God only has that right and privilege. Thinking is, 
or ought to be, a coolness and a calmness; and our poor hearts throb, and our 
poor brains beat too much for that. And yet, I’ve sometimes thought my brain 
was very calm—frozen calm, this old skull cracks so, like a glass in which 
the contents turned to ice, and shiver it. And still this hair is growing now; 
